column15: Using a t-test and the null hypothesis mu=2.01 and alternate hypothesis mu=/=2.01, I find a p-value of 0.0109, which is the probability of getting the given results or more extreme under the assumptions that the period is 2.01 seconds. Since this is vary unlikely to be a result of random error, I do not support the prediction and I reject the null hypothesis.
